    "summary": "Tarila Marclint Ebiede is a Program and Project Advisor and Researcher working in the field of Peacebuilding, Conflict and Insecurity.  He has conducted research on themes such as disarmament, demobilisation and reintegration of ex-combatants, youth agency in conflict affected societies in Africa,  non-state armed groups and governance in conflict affected societies, election violence, and post-conflict politics. He holds a PhD in Social Sciences from KU Leuven, Belgium. His teaching is mainly focused on Africa\u2019s International Relations and Politics. Highly skilled in research, project evaluation and policy analysis in the area of governance, development, youth employment, reintegration and community mobilisation. His research has been funded by the European Union Marie Curie fund for Sustainable Peacebuilding, American Political Science Association (APSA), United States Institute for Peace (USIP) and Centre for African Studies at the University of Edinburgh. He has provided technical assistance and advisory to institutions such as the European Union and the United Nations Office on Drug and Crime (UNODC) on Conflict Sensitivity, Maritime Security and Crime Prevention. He is co-founder of Conflict Research Network \u2013 West Africa (CORN \u2013 West Africa), a multi-disciplinary network for peace and conflict studies scholars based in West Africa.",
